#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:5
msgid "Using via `numpy.distutils`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:15
msgid ""
":mod:`numpy.distutils` is part of NumPy, and extends the standard Python "
"``distutils`` module to deal with Fortran sources and F2PY signature files, "
"e.g. compile Fortran sources, call F2PY to construct extension modules, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:-1
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:21
msgid ""
"Consider the following ``setup_file.py`` for the ``fib`` and ``scalar`` "
"examples from :ref:`f2py-getting-started` section:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:24
msgid ""
"from numpy.distutils.core import Extension\n"
"\n"
"ext1 = Extension(name = 'scalar',\n"
"                 sources = ['scalar.f'])\n"
"ext2 = Extension(name = 'fib2',\n"
"                 sources = ['fib2.pyf', 'fib1.f'])\n"
"\n"
"if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n"
"    from numpy.distutils.core import setup\n"
"    setup(name = 'f2py_example',\n"
"          description       = \"F2PY Users Guide examples\",\n"
"          author            = \"Pearu Peterson\",\n"
"          author_email      = \"pearu@cens.ioc.ee\",\n"
"          ext_modules = [ext1, ext2]\n"
"          )\n"
"# End of setup_example.py\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:27
msgid "Running"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:29
msgid "python setup_example.py build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:33
msgid ""
"will build two extension modules ``scalar`` and ``fib2`` to the build "
"directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:37
msgid "Extensions to ``distutils``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:39
msgid ""
":mod:`numpy.distutils` extends ``distutils`` with the following features:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:41
msgid ""
":class:`Extension` class argument ``sources`` may contain Fortran source "
"files. In addition, the list ``sources`` may contain at most one F2PY "
"signature file, and in this case, the name of an Extension module must match "
"with the ``<modulename>`` used in signature file. It is assumed that an F2PY "
"signature file contains exactly one ``python module`` block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:48
msgid ""
"If ``sources`` do not contain a signature file, then F2PY is used to scan "
"Fortran source files to construct wrappers to the Fortran codes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:51
msgid ""
"Additional options to the F2PY executable can be given using the :class:"
"`Extension` class argument ``f2py_options``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:54
msgid "The following new ``distutils`` commands are defined:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:56
msgid "``build_src``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:57
msgid ""
"to construct Fortran wrapper extension modules, among many other things."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:59
msgid "``config_fc``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:59
msgid "to change Fortran compiler options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:61
msgid ""
"Additionally, the ``build_ext`` and ``build_clib`` commands are also "
"enhanced to support Fortran sources."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:64
msgid "Run"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:66
msgid "python <setup.py file> config_fc build_src build_ext --help"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:70
msgid "to see available options for these commands."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:72
msgid ""
"When building Python packages containing Fortran sources, one can choose "
"different Fortran compilers by using the ``build_ext`` command option ``--"
"fcompiler=<Vendor>``. Here ``<Vendor>`` can be one of the following names "
"(on ``linux`` systems)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:77
msgid ""
"absoft compaq fujitsu g95 gnu gnu95 intel intele intelem lahey nag nagfor nv "
"pathf95 pg vast"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:79
msgid ""
"See ``numpy_distutils/fcompiler.py`` for an up-to-date list of supported "
"compilers for different platforms, or run"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/distutils.rst:82
msgid "python -m numpy.f2py -c --backend distutils --help-fcompiler"
msgstr ""
